Conditions
Conditions let programs make decisions.
if (grade &gt;= 90) {
  print("That’s great")
} else if (grade &gt;= 70) {
  print("You passed")
} else {
  print("We got some work to do!")
}

Practice

What message prints if grade &lt;- 75?


"You passed"

Loops
Loops repeat code until a condition is met.

While Loop
x &lt;- 1
while (x &lt; 7) {
  x &lt;- x + 1
}


For Loop
for (i in 1:7) {
  x &lt;- i
}






Warning



If vectorized code works, prefer it over loops.

Functions
Functions package reusable logic.
convert_in_cm &lt;- function(measurement, unit) {
  if (unit == "in") {
    conversion &lt;- measurement * 2.54
  } else if (unit == "cm") {
    conversion &lt;- measurement / 2.54
  }
  return(conversion)
}
convert_in_cm(5, "in")

Practice

What are the arguments of convert_in_cm()?


measurement and unit
